20%3C%2Ftr%3E%0A%20%20%3Ctr%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%3Ctd%3ELow%20Amplitude%3C%2Ftd%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%3Ctd%20id%3D%22amp%22%20class%3D%22sliderCell%22%3E%3Cdiv%20style%3D%22position%3A%20relative%3B%20width%3A%20100%25%3B%20height%3A%20100%25%3B%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22slider%22%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ccanvas%20width%3D%22619%22%20height%3D%2237%22%20style%3D%22position%3A%20absolute%3B%20top%3A%200px%3B%20left%3A%200px%3B%20width%3A%20100%25%3B%20height%3A%20100%25%3B%20z-index%3A%201%3B%22%3E%3C%2Fcanvas%3E%3Ccanvas%20width%3D%22619%22%20height%3D%2237%22%20style%3D%22position%3A%20absolute%3B%20top%3A%200px%3B%20left%3A%200px%3B%20width%3A%20100%25%3B%20height%3A%20100%25%3B%20z-index%3A%202%3B%22%3E%3C%2Fcanvas%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%3Ctd%3EHigh%20Amplitude%3C%2Ftd%3E%0A%20%20%3C%2Ftr%3E%0A%3C%2Ftbody%3E%3C%2Ftable%3E%0A%0A%3Ch3%3EWhat%20is%20this%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20This%20is%20an%20audio%20generator%20tool%20to%20explore%20the%20timbral%20quality%20imparted%0A%20%20by%20applying%20one%20of%20several%20filters%20to%20an%20incoming%20signal.%20The%20top%20box%0A%20%20is%20an%20oscilloscope%20view%20which%20visualizes%20the%20waveform%2C%20and%20the%20bottom%0A%20%20box%20is%20a%20harmonic%20spectrum%20view.%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20This%20tool%20generates%20white%20noise%20at%20an%20adjustable%20amplitude%2C%20and%20allows%0A%20%20you%20to%20adjust%20the%20type%20and%20parameters%20of%20the%20filter%2C%20as%20well%20the%0A%20%20overall%20output%20amplitude%20(volume).%20The%20filter%20parameters%20are%3A%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cul%3E%0A%20%20%3Cli%3E%3Ci%3Ef%3Csub%3E0%3C%2Fsub%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20(center%20frequency)%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ci%3Ef%3Csub%3E0%3C%2Fsub%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%0A%20%20%20%20is%20the%20frequency%20at%20which%20the%20filter%20is%20most%20active%20and%20at%20which%0A%20%20%20%20the%20frequency%20response%20of%20the%20filter%20%22pivots.%22%0A%20%20%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%20%20%3Cli%3E%3Ci%3EQ%3C%2Fi%3E%20(quality)%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ci%3EQ%3C%2Fi%3E%20is%20a%20measure%20of%20how%20steep%20the%0A%20%20%20%20dropoff%20is%20of%20the%20frequency%20response%20curve%20around%0A%20%20%20%20%3Ci%3Ef%3Csub%3E0%3C%2Fsub%3E%3C%2Fi%3E.%20A%20low%20%3Ci%3EQ%3C%2Fi%3E%20means%20that%20the%0A%20%20%20%20frequency%20curve%20ramps%20gently%20down%2C%20such%20that%20the%20filter%20encompasses%0A%20%20%20%20a%20relatively%20wider%20portion%20of%20the%20spectrum.%20A%20high%20%3Ci%3EQ%3C%2Fi%3E%20means%0A%20%20%20%20that%20the%20frequency%20curve%20ramps%20steeply%20down%2C%20such%20that%20the%0A%20%20%20%20filter%20encompasses%20a%20relatively%20narrower%20portion%20of%20the%0A%20%20%20%20spectrum.%20%3Ci%3EQ%3C%2Fi%3E%20must%20be%20a%20positive%20(non-zero)%20value.%0A%20%20%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%20%20%3Cli%3Etype%20%E2%80%94%20There%20are%20four%20basic%20types%20of%20filter.%20In%20each%0A%20%20%20%20case%2C%20the%20filter%20performs%20a%20transformation%20from%20its%20input%20harmonic%0A%20%20%20%20spectrum%2C%20with%20a%20%22pivot%22%20at%20%3Ci%3Ef%3Csub%3E0%3C%2Fsub%3E%3C%2Fi%3E.%20The%20filter%0A%20%20%20%20type%20indicates%20the%20general%20shape%20of%20the%20transformation%3A%0A%20%20%20%20%3Cul%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cli%3Elow-pass%20%E2%80%94%20The%20filter%20passes%20(allows)%20frequencies%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20lower%20than%20%3Ci%3Ef%3Csub%3E0%3C%2Fsub%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20and%20rejects%20(squelches)%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20frequencies%20above%20%3Ci%3Ef%3Csub%3E0%3C%2Fsub%3E%3C%2Fi%3E.%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cli%3Ehigh-pass%20%E2%80%94%20The%20filter%20passes%20frequencies%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20higher%20than%20%3Ci%3Ef%3Csub%3E0%3C%2Fsub%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20and%20rejects%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20frequencies%20below%20%3Ci%3Ef%3Csub%3E0%3C%2Fsub%3E%3C%2Fi%3E.%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cli%3Eband-pass%20%E2%80%94%20The%20filter%20passes%20frequencies%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20near%20%3Ci%3Ef%3Csub%3E0%3C%2Fsub%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20and%20rejects%20frequencies%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20away%20from%20%3Ci%3Ef%3Csub%3E0%3C%2Fsub%3E%3C%2Fi%3E.%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cli%3Enotch%20(band-reject)%20%E2%80%94%20The%20filter%20passes%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20frequencies%20away%20from%20%3Ci%3Ef%3Csub%3E0%3C%2Fsub%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20and%20rejects%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20frequencies%20near%20%3Ci%3Ef%3Csub%3E0%3C%2Fsub%3E%3C%2Fi%3E.%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%3C%2Ful%3E%0A%20%20%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%3C%2Ful%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.com%2Fdanfuzz%2Fmimu%2Ftree%2Fmain%2Ffilter-explorer%22%3E%0A%20%20See%20the%20source%3C%2Fa%3E.%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Ch3%3EItems%20of%20note%3C%2Fh3%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20Because%20%3Ci%3EQ%3C%2Fi%3E%20is%20not%20allowed%20to%20be%20zero%2C%20when%20you%20adjust%20its%0A%20%20slider%20all%20the%20way%20down%2C%20you%20instead%20get%20a%20small%20but%20positive%20value.%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20There%20is%20no%20upper%20limit%20to%20%3Ci%3EQ%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20but%20this%20demo%20limits%20it%20to%0A%20%20500.%20This%20more%20or%20less%20covers%20the%20useful%20range%20for%20sound%20synthesis.%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20At%20higher%20%3Ci%3EQ%3C%2Fi%3E%20the%20filter%20becomes%20significantly%20%22resonant.%22%20That%20is%2C%0A%20%20even%20if%20you%20cut%20off%20the%20input%20(by%20setting%20the%20amplitude%20to%20zero)%2C%20you%0A%20%20will%20still%20see%20output%20with%20energy%20at%20%3Ci%3Ef%3Csub%3E0%3C%2Fsub%3E%3C%2Fi%3E.%20It%20will%0A%20%20eventually%20decay.%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20It%20can%20be%20hard%20to%20tell%20what%20a%20notch%20filter%20is%20doing%20at%20higher%20%3Ci%3EQ%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%0A%20%20both%20audibly%20and%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20spectrum.%20When%20using%20a%20notch%20filter%2C%0A%20%20you'll%20probably%20have%20better%20results%20with%20%3Ci%3EQ%3C%2Fi%3E%20under%205.%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20It's%20easy%20to%20pick%20filter%20parameters%20which%20will%20%22blow%20out%22%20the%20output%0A%20%20out%20of%20the%20valid-for-audio%20range%20of%20-1%20to%201.%20The%20straightforward%20way%0A%20%20to%20correct%20for%20this%20is%20simply%20to%20lower%20either%20the%20input%20or%20output%0A%20%20amplitude.%20If%20you%20don't%2C%20the%20main%20thing%20you%20will%20notice%20is%20that%20you%0A%20%20end%20up%20with%20extra%20peaks%20in%20the%20output%20harmonics%2C%20which%20correspond%20to%0A%20%20the%20%22shelves%22%20caused%20by%20the%20cutoff%20of%20the%20waveform%20at%20either%20extreme%20of%0A%20%20instantaneous%20amplitude.%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20The%20filters%20implemented%20in%20this%20demo%20are%20two-pole%20infinite%20impulse%0A%20%20response%20(IIR)%20filter.%20The%20%22infinite%22%20in%20the%20name%20means%20that%20filter%0A%20%20output%20at%20any%20given%20point%20in%20time%20depends%20on%20%3Ci%3Eall%3C%2Fi%3E%20of%20the%0A%20%20input%20that%20the%20filter%20has%20ever%20received.%20This%20is%20in%20contrast%20to%20a%0A%20%20finite%20impulse%20response%20(FIR)%20filter%2C%20which%20only%20depends%20on%20a%0A%20%20limited%20rolling%20window%20of%20previous%20input%20to%20the%20filter.%20(In%20digital%0A%20%20filters%2C%20this%20window%20is%20generally%20one%20sample%20per%20pole.)%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20The%20four%20basic%20types%20of%20filter%20demonstrated%20here%20aren't%20the%20only%20kinds%20of%0A%20%20filter.%20There%20are%20many%20others.%20Roughly%20speaking%2C%20though%2C%20one%20can%20think%0A%20%20of%20any%20filter%20as%20a%20combination%20of%20the%20types%20described%20here.%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Ctable%20class%3D%22footer%22%3E%0A%20%20%3Ctbody%3E%3Ctr%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%3Ctd%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20Copyright%202015-2025%20the%20Mimu%20Authors%20(Dan%20Bornstein%20et%20alia).%3Cbr%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20SPDX-License-Identifier%3A%20Apache-2.0%0A%20%20%20%20%3C%2Ftd%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%3Ctd%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fmilk.com%2F%22%3Emilk.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20%2F%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22..%